      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw model. Production mesh (≈420,000 elements, hex-dominant) yields QoI values within 1.1% of the finest mesh. GCI estimated at 1.4% for stiffness QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error below 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson convergence monitored across all 120 load increments. Maximum force residual 3.2e-8; energy balance error 0.04%. No unconverged increments. Direct solver used for contact-dominated steps."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts reviewed by a second analyst independent of the model builder. Discrepancies resolved prior to validation comparison.",
      "rationale": "Independent review checklist completed by senior FEA engineer. Three minor boundary condition clarifications identified and corrected before final run. Post-processing Python scripts version-controlled and peer-reviewed. No use errors propagated to final results."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions (linear elasticity for titanium alloy, frictional contact at screw-rod interface, rigid loading fixtures) justified by literature and sensitivity analysis demonstrating negligible impact of plasticity onset on QoIs within the validated load range.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V modeled as linear elastic to yield; ASTM F1717 protocol does not require post-yield characterization for stiffness and yield force QoIs. Frictional contact (μ=0.2) sensitivity study showed <3% QoI change over μ∈[0.15, 0.30]. Model form uncertainty propagated into E/uval calculation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
