      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certificate of conformance lot testing for the specific Ti-6Al-4V bar stock used in the N=11 experimental constructs. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of representative hardware.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114.2 GPa) and yield strength (896 MPa) from lot CoC tensile testing (n=3 specimens). CMM measurements of screw OD, thread pitch, and rod diameter used to update nominal CAD geometry. Dimensional uncertainty included in uval budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental constructs (N=11) assembled from production-representative hardware with documented lot traceability. Sample size sufficient to estimate mean QoIs with coefficient of variation characterization.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled using production screws (Lot 2023-A) and rods (Lot 2023-B) per ASTM F1717 assembly protocol. CoV for stiffness 3.1%, yield force 4.4%, force at 40 mm 5.2%. Traceability records archived. Six constructs tested at Lab 1, five at Lab 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate the full range of COU loading scenarios including at minimum two offset distances per ASTM F1717.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single offset distance (50 mm) per ASTM F1717 standard configuration. COU requires only the standard F1717 configuration for the intended submission; however, the single test condition limits generalizability. Achieved level 2 acknowledged; risk accepted given COU scope restriction to standard offset."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions, loading) demonstrably equivalent to experimental test conditions within quantified tolerances.",
      "rationale": "One-to-one mapping documented between FEA inputs and experimental parameters. Geometric equivalency confirmed via CMM overlay. Load application point and fixture stiffness matched to test machine compliance measurements. Equivalency table reviewed and approved by test laboratory."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric; acceptance threshold E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs. Percent difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs satisfy acceptance criteria: stiffness E/uval=0.81 (4.2% diff), yield force E/uval=1.44 (6.8% diff), force at 40 mm E/uval=1.61 (7.3% diff). Validation uncertainty budget includes experimental measurement uncertainty, model input uncertainty, and numerical error. Metrics computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly relevant to the clinical and regulatory decision regarding construct mechanical performance under compression-bending.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 QoIs are the regulatory standard for pedicle screw construct characterization. Stiffness predicts load sharing; yield force predicts onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm predicts ultimate construct behavior. All three are cited in FDA guidance for Class II spinal fixation systems."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
